Basic Linux Commands

1.Display current date and time.

Syntax:date
It displays the currewnt date and time.
output:
[24bcs105@mepcolinux linux]$date
Tue Feb 25 17:00:32 IST 2025

2.Display only the month name of the current date.

Syntax:date +"%B"
It displays the current date's month only.
output:
[24bcs105@mepcolinux linux]$date +"%B"
February

3.Commands to create directory and file.

Syntax:mkdir(directory name)
It creates the directory.
Syntax:touch(file name)
It creates the file.
output:
[24bcs105@mepcolinux linux]$mkdir linux1
[24bcs105@mepcolinux linux]$touch f1.txt
[24bcs105@mepcolinux linux]$ls
f1.txt  linux1

4.Display your own username.

Syntax:whoami
It displays the own username.
output:
[24bcs105@mepcolinux linux]$whoami
24bcs105

5.Display the list of current users and your username.

Syntax:who
It displays the list of current users.
output:
[24bcs105@mepcolinux linux]$who
