6.Display the manual pages for date command page by page.

Syntax:man date
It displays the manual pages for date command.
output:
[24bcs105@mepcolinux linux]$man date
NAME
       date - print or set the system date and time

SYNOPSIS
       date [OPTION]... [+FORMAT]
       date [-u|--utc|--universal] [MMDDhhmm[[CC]YY][.ss]]

7.Display the system name in the network.

Syntax:hostname
It displays the host of the system.
output:
[24bcs105@mepcolinux linux]$hostname
mepcolinux.mepcoeng.ac.in

8.Print your name on terminal using echo.

Syntax:echo
It prints the name.
output:
[24bcs105@mepcolinux linux]$echo Kamalesh
Kamalesh

